"biography": {
"early_life": "Liam Mairi was the son of Lord Isaac Mairi and Colonel Mairi in Tyrrendor. His mother was executed for her involvement in a rebellion, and his father was killed the same day. Liam was fostered by Duke Lindell in Tirvainne alongside Xaden Riorson. Xaden taught Liam to fight in preparation for joining the Riders Quadrant. Liam had a younger sister, Sloane, but they were separated after their father was executed."
},
"physical_description": "Liam is tall, with spiky light-blond hair, a prominent nose, and blue eyes. He has a sprawling rebellion relic on his wrist that extends under his sleeve. He is as tall as Sawyer and as built as Dain, with a dimpled smile.",
"personality": "Liam is fiercely loyal, charming, and has a good sense of humor. He is well-liked, open, and honest about his past. Despite his hardships, he maintains dignity and a positive attitude.",
"powers_and_abilities": {
"powers": {
"lesser_magic": "Liam can use Lesser Magic to open doors, move with preternatural speed, manipulate mage lights, and power ink pens. He can also place runes.",
"signet": "Liam's signet, Farsight, allows him to see great distances and through obscuring elements like fog. His pupils dilate when he uses this ability."
},},},],

